WEBVTT

00:05.291 --> 00:08.625
♪ dramatic music ♪

00:08.625 --> 00:10.208
[Ray] Previously
on  Ray Donovan...

00:10.208 --> 00:12.000
[Ray] How long?

00:12.000 --> 00:13.041
[Friedman] As I said,
it's not precise.

00:13.041 --> 00:16.041
Three? Six? What?

00:16.041 --> 00:17.375
In that range.

00:17.375 --> 00:20.333
I gotta make it to Christmas.

00:20.333 --> 00:23.166
What do you mean,
you gotta make it to Christmas?

00:23.166 --> 00:24.709
You know, for the kids.

00:25.750 --> 00:27.625
I wanna stop treatment.

00:27.625 --> 00:29.875
[Ray] No, you don't.

00:29.875 --> 00:33.041
You're just tired,
that's all.

00:33.041 --> 00:35.208
I know how hard
this has been for you.

00:35.208 --> 00:36.959
You don't know.

00:39.041 --> 00:42.625
This...

00:42.625 --> 00:46.417
this is some Godless
fucking bullshit

00:46.417 --> 00:48.208
is what this is.

00:48.208 --> 00:52.375
♪♪♪

00:59.709 --> 01:02.166
♪ The boy was in the hallway
drinking a glass of tea ♪

01:02.166 --> 01:04.542
♪ From the other end
of the hallway ♪

01:04.542 --> 01:06.375
♪ A rhythm was generating ♪

01:06.375 --> 01:09.375
♪ Another boy was sliding
up the hallway ♪

01:09.375 --> 01:14.500
♪ He merged perfectly
with the hallway ♪

01:14.500 --> 01:16.333
♪ He merged perfectly,
the mirror... ♪

01:16.333 --> 01:21.208
[Terry] I got it from
the Rose Bowl Flea Market.

01:21.208 --> 01:24.500
Only 39 bucks.

01:24.500 --> 01:25.375
You like it?

01:25.750 --> 01:28.375
I do, honey.

01:28.375 --> 01:30.166
♪ He pushed him
against the locker ♪

01:30.166 --> 01:31.083
♪ He drove it in,
he drove it home ♪

01:31.083 --> 01:33.250
♪ He drove it deep
in Johnny ♪

01:33.250 --> 01:35.000
♪ The boy disappeared ♪

01:35.000 --> 01:37.208
♪ Johnny fell on his knees ♪

01:37.208 --> 01:39.333
♪ Started crashing his head
against the locker ♪

01:39.333 --> 01:41.542
♪ Started crashing
his head against the locker ♪

01:41.542 --> 01:44.250
- Come on, hurry up already.
- Just hold it still, Bunch.

01:44.250 --> 01:45.291
[drill whirs]

01:45.291 --> 01:47.458
Ray.

01:47.458 --> 01:48.291
Fuckin' be careful.

01:48.291 --> 01:50.208
There's nobody's
holding the ladder.

01:50.208 --> 01:51.583
[Ray] Almost done.

01:51.583 --> 01:52.917
All right,
you can let it go.

01:52.917 --> 01:55.250
- You sure?
- Yeah.

01:55.250 --> 01:57.000
[cell phone rings]

01:57.000 --> 01:58.625
- [Ray] Huh?
- [Bunchy] All right.

01:58.625 --> 02:01.417
Hold this for me.

02:01.417 --> 02:02.458
Hello?

02:02.458 --> 02:03.792
[Bunchy] Careful.

02:05.083 --> 02:06.959
Yeah, this is she.

02:06.959 --> 02:08.625
[drill whirs]

02:08.625 --> 02:10.959
[Bunchy and Ray
speaking indistinctly]

02:10.959 --> 02:11.250
What does that mean?

02:17.709 --> 02:20.417
No, I understand.

02:24.291 --> 02:26.500
Thank you for calling. I...

02:26.500 --> 02:28.625
appreciate everything
you've done.

02:29.583 --> 02:30.875
Bye.

02:32.125 --> 02:33.834
All right, plug it in!

02:35.125 --> 02:36.959
I'm gonna go
for a little walk.

02:36.959 --> 02:39.291
Sure.

02:39.291 --> 02:41.083
♪ The boy was in the hallway
drinking a glass of tea... ♪

02:41.083 --> 02:43.125
- [Bunchy] Did you plug it in?
- [Beckett] Yeah.

02:43.125 --> 02:45.583
[Bunchy] No, you fuckin' didn't,
'cause it's not on.

02:45.583 --> 02:49.417
♪ Another boy was sliding
up the hallway ♪

02:49.417 --> 02:54.000
♪ He merged perfectly
with the hallway ♪

02:54.000 --> 02:57.667
♪ He merged perfectly,
the mirror in the hallway ♪

02:57.667 --> 03:01.917
♪ The boy looked at Johnny,
Johnny wanted to run ♪

03:01.917 --> 03:04.959
♪ But the movie kept moving
as planned ♪

03:04.959 --> 03:07.041
♪ The boy took Johnny ♪

03:07.041 --> 03:08.834
♪ He pushed him
against the locker ♪

03:08.834 --> 03:10.667
♪ He drove it in,
he drove it home ♪

03:10.667 --> 03:12.792
♪ He drove it deep
in Johnny ♪

03:12.792 --> 03:15.834
♪ The boy disappeared,
Johnny fell on his knees ♪

03:15.834 --> 03:16.750
♪ Started crashing
his head... ♪

03:16.750 --> 03:18.709
[man] Yes.

03:18.709 --> 03:20.542
But the patient
is here right now.

03:20.542 --> 03:22.875
I do not want her to have
to come back a second time.

03:22.875 --> 03:26.709
♪ When suddenly ♪

03:26.709 --> 03:29.709
♪ Johnny gets the feeling ♪

03:29.709 --> 03:32.166
♪ He's being surrounded by ♪

03:32.166 --> 03:34.667
♪ Horses, horses,
horses, horses... ♪

03:34.667 --> 03:36.375
So I, uh...

03:36.375 --> 03:39.125
[continues inaudibly]

03:39.125 --> 03:40.792
♪ Coming in
in all directions ♪

03:40.792 --> 03:43.709
♪ White shining
silver studs ♪

03:43.709 --> 03:46.709
♪ With their nose
in flames ♪

03:46.709 --> 03:49.208
♪ He saw horses, horses ♪

03:49.208 --> 03:52.041
♪ Horses, horses, horses ♪

03:52.041 --> 03:54.792
[door opens]

03:54.792 --> 03:56.375
[sniffles]

03:56.375 --> 04:00.291
Place is starting
to look good, huh?

04:00.291 --> 04:01.834
What?

04:01.834 --> 04:03.750
Except for that fucking sign,
but...

04:03.750 --> 04:06.083
we should be able
to get that up tomorrow.

04:11.417 --> 04:11.583
You all right?

04:14.792 --> 04:17.458
I'm just tired.

04:17.458 --> 04:19.041
Sure.

04:27.500 --> 04:29.291
Close your eyes.

04:29.291 --> 04:30.250
Why?

04:30.250 --> 04:32.417
I got something for you.

04:32.417 --> 04:33.667
Surprise.

04:33.667 --> 04:35.333
[sighs]

04:35.333 --> 04:36.250
I don't want any more surprises.

04:36.250 --> 04:39.041
Just close your fuckin' eyes.

04:47.959 --> 04:50.625
- What is it?
- Shh.

05:06.458 --> 05:08.250
It's beautiful.

05:11.834 --> 05:14.166
What am I gonna do with it?

05:14.166 --> 05:16.125
What do you mean,
what are you gonna do with it?

05:16.125 --> 05:19.041
You're gonna wear it tomorrow
night for the opening party.

05:19.667 --> 05:22.083
Sweetheart, for one party?

05:22.083 --> 05:25.291
[chuckling] One party?

05:25.291 --> 05:29.458
No, you wear it tomorrow,

05:29.458 --> 05:32.125
Conor's graduation,

05:32.125 --> 05:33.917
Bridget's wedding,

05:33.917 --> 05:35.000
our 50th fuckin'
wedding anniversary,

05:35.000 --> 05:37.250
if I live that long.

05:38.709 --> 05:40.083
Thanks, Ray.

05:40.083 --> 05:41.166
[sighs]

05:41.166 --> 05:42.500
It was very thoughtful.

05:48.542 --> 05:50.000
[sighs]

05:50.000 --> 05:53.000
♪ somber music ♪

05:53.000 --> 05:58.917
♪♪♪

06:00.583 --> 06:01.000
[faucet runs]

06:01.000 --> 06:03.792
[sniffles]

06:05.834 --> 06:10.709
♪♪♪

06:33.625 --> 06:34.709
Ray? [clears throat]

06:42.333 --> 06:43.750
Ray?

06:46.041 --> 06:47.542
- You say something?
- [faucet shuts off]

06:54.041 --> 06:56.291
We didn't get into
the Sloan Kettering trial.

06:56.291 --> 06:56.709
[sniffles]

07:00.291 --> 07:02.583
What?

07:02.583 --> 07:04.875
Bergstein called.

07:04.875 --> 07:06.834
When?

07:06.834 --> 07:09.417
Earlier.

07:09.417 --> 07:12.625
They selected three patients
for surgery.

07:12.625 --> 07:14.250
But I'm not one of them.

07:14.250 --> 07:16.667
What do you--

07:16.667 --> 07:19.625
what do you mean,
you're not one of them?

07:19.625 --> 07:21.959
They called you?

07:21.959 --> 07:24.041
- Yeah, her office did.
- What the fuck?

07:24.041 --> 07:28.083
- They're not supposed to--
- Ray.

07:28.083 --> 07:29.834
I mean, who tells someone

07:29.834 --> 07:30.583
they're a perfect fuckin'
candidate and then just--

07:30.583 --> 07:33.417
Yes, but, uh,
it was a lottery.

07:33.417 --> 07:35.709
And we didn't get in.

07:45.667 --> 07:46.750
I'm relieved.

07:50.375 --> 07:53.458
That long list of stuff
that could happen to me...

07:53.458 --> 07:58.458
[sighs] The blindness
and strokes...

07:58.458 --> 08:03.041
I don't wanna have
to worry about that.

08:03.041 --> 08:05.667
I just wanna open the bar.

08:05.667 --> 08:08.625
Everybody's gonna be there.

08:08.625 --> 08:12.625
We'll drink whiskey
and sing songs.

08:12.625 --> 08:15.041
And I can say good-bye.

08:16.792 --> 08:19.125
And you'll be by my side,

08:19.125 --> 08:21.417
holding my hand.

08:25.333 --> 08:28.375
What are those?

08:28.375 --> 08:29.625
Seconal.
I picked it up earlier.

08:32.750 --> 08:33.792
What for?

08:36.375 --> 08:37.834
You know what for.

08:58.333 --> 09:00.875
Shouldn't have done that.

09:06.375 --> 09:08.917
What are you doing?

09:08.917 --> 09:10.667
Going to New York.

09:10.667 --> 09:11.667
I don't want you to go
to New York.

09:11.667 --> 09:14.750
Talk to that doctor,
sort this out.

09:14.750 --> 09:16.792
[sighs]

09:20.542 --> 09:22.709
Ray, remember what we said
if the trial didn't work out?

09:25.500 --> 09:29.000
That I could control
how this ends.

09:29.000 --> 09:30.500
Ray.

09:32.041 --> 09:34.458
You're getting that fuckin'
surgery, Abby.

09:34.458 --> 09:37.458
You don't get to tell me
what to do with my fuckin' body.

09:45.458 --> 09:47.542
Abs, I know how much
pain you're in.

09:48.750 --> 09:51.333
I know how hard
this is for you.

09:51.333 --> 09:53.458
But we're gonna beat it.

09:53.458 --> 09:55.000
All right?

09:55.000 --> 09:57.375
I promise.

09:57.375 --> 09:58.792
You hear me?

09:59.709 --> 10:02.333
And ten years from now,
we're gonna be

10:02.333 --> 10:03.792
sitting in that fuckin' bar,
having a drink,

10:03.792 --> 10:06.417
laughing about it.

10:06.417 --> 10:08.125
Understand?

10:10.667 --> 10:12.083
Abby.

10:16.625 --> 10:19.375
- Yeah.
- I love you, sweetheart.

10:22.041 --> 10:23.625
I love you too.

10:25.834 --> 10:26.291
All right.

10:26.291 --> 10:31.583
♪♪♪

10:31.583 --> 10:34.667
[cell phone ringing and buzzing]

10:36.125 --> 10:37.792
Yeah.

10:37.792 --> 10:39.083
You told me you swapped out
Abby's number.

10:39.083 --> 10:41.417
[sighs]

10:41.417 --> 10:42.750
- What?
- In the database.

10:42.750 --> 10:44.250
The fuckin'
Sloan Kettering thing.

10:44.250 --> 10:45.583
You told me you gave them
your number

10:45.583 --> 10:46.792
- instead of hers.
- I did.

10:46.792 --> 10:50.041
So why the fuck
are they calling her, Lena?

10:50.041 --> 10:51.709
Ray, what are you
talking about?

10:51.709 --> 10:54.041
[sighs]

10:54.041 --> 10:56.000
She didn't get into the trial.

10:57.083 --> 10:59.041
Oh, fuck, Ray.
I'm so sorry.

10:59.041 --> 11:01.083
- I wanna know who did.
- What do you want me to do?

11:01.083 --> 11:02.667
I want the names.
I want the fuckin' addresses.

11:02.667 --> 11:04.792
I want everything.
You understand me, Lena?

11:04.792 --> 11:06.291
- Yeah.
- [phone beeps]

11:06.291 --> 11:09.333
♪ dark music ♪

11:09.333 --> 11:15.166
♪♪♪

11:17.333 --> 11:18.000
Did you get the tickets?

11:18.000 --> 11:19.959
Y-yeah, they're right there.

11:21.000 --> 11:24.375
- What about the trial?
- Uh, that took a minute,

11:24.375 --> 11:26.750
but I cracked it.

11:26.750 --> 11:28.792
These are copies of all
their hospital files,

11:28.792 --> 11:31.667
all the medical histories,
addresses, and workplaces.

11:33.000 --> 11:35.166
[Avi]
So what time's the flight?

11:36.709 --> 11:38.583
11:59.

11:47.625 --> 11:48.959
Where's your bag?

11:50.125 --> 11:51.291
It's in the car.

11:52.291 --> 11:53.208
Let's go.

11:58.375 --> 11:59.542
You all right?

11:59.542 --> 12:01.083
I'm all right.

12:02.875 --> 12:05.834
[indistinct chatter]

12:13.959 --> 12:16.625
[sighs]

12:34.041 --> 12:35.375
[laughs, sniffles]

12:35.375 --> 12:37.417
[groans]

12:37.417 --> 12:39.709
You all right?

12:39.709 --> 12:42.125
Yeah. The Santa Ana winds.

12:42.125 --> 12:46.375
Every year, same bullshit
with my sinuses. [sniffles]

12:46.375 --> 12:48.041
Kills me.

12:50.542 --> 12:54.917
So your contact,
who is she?

12:54.917 --> 12:55.750
I can't tell you that.

12:55.750 --> 12:59.458
Just...she has access
to a lab.

12:59.458 --> 13:02.333
- Where?
- Columbia.

13:04.250 --> 13:06.125
You sure she's gonna help us?

13:07.375 --> 13:10.000
We go back.

13:10.000 --> 13:14.125
She's not happy about
breaking cover, but...

13:14.125 --> 13:16.417
we go back.

13:16.417 --> 13:17.625
What's she got?

13:17.625 --> 13:20.959
Don't worry about it.

13:20.959 --> 13:22.583
What is it, Av?

13:23.625 --> 13:26.458
- You sure wanna know?
- Yeah, I wanna know.

13:26.458 --> 13:28.000
[sighs]

13:28.000 --> 13:29.125
Meningitis bacteria.

13:33.583 --> 13:35.250
[Avi] What?

13:35.250 --> 13:38.417
Will it kill him?

13:38.417 --> 13:41.667
No, it won't kill him.

13:41.667 --> 13:44.959
But it will definitely
disqualify him from the trial.

13:49.458 --> 13:52.709
[door opens]

13:59.000 --> 14:00.500
Hey.

14:00.500 --> 14:03.792
Pool table's in.

14:03.792 --> 14:05.750
Jesus, it's hot in here.

14:05.750 --> 14:07.625
Oh, yeah?

14:07.625 --> 14:09.000
[sniffles]

14:09.000 --> 14:11.667
I can't feel it.
I'm fuckin' freezing.

14:11.667 --> 14:13.834
Ooh.

14:13.834 --> 14:14.000
Come here.

14:22.083 --> 14:23.792
What's going on?

14:26.500 --> 14:28.834
Ray threw away my pills.

14:28.834 --> 14:30.500
What pills?

14:30.500 --> 14:32.709
My suicide pills.

14:33.291 --> 14:35.750
What?

14:37.959 --> 14:39.166
I didn't get into the trial.

14:41.375 --> 14:43.083
Shit.

14:47.709 --> 14:53.125
So he's on a plane
to New York,

14:53.125 --> 14:55.041
trying to fix things.

14:55.041 --> 14:57.417
Well, that's
the right thing to do.

14:57.417 --> 14:58.333
We all want
the same thing, honey.

14:58.333 --> 15:00.250
He's just trying
to make you better.

15:01.417 --> 15:05.625
Does anyone in this family
give a fuck about what I want?

15:08.750 --> 15:10.083
My doctor rewrote
the prescription.

15:13.875 --> 15:16.041
I need you to pick it up.

15:17.208 --> 15:20.542
Well, let me call Ray.
You two can work this out.

15:20.542 --> 15:21.709
No.

15:22.875 --> 15:26.667
It's better if he's not here.

15:26.667 --> 15:29.917
[sighs]

15:29.917 --> 15:32.083
That prescription was
the only thing keeping me sane.

15:36.750 --> 15:39.250
I need you to pick it up.

15:42.458 --> 15:45.917
Can you do that for me?

15:45.917 --> 15:49.291
♪ somber music ♪

15:49.291 --> 15:51.208
[horn blaring]

15:55.083 --> 15:58.083
[siren wailing]

15:58.083 --> 16:02.291
♪♪♪

16:23.041 --> 16:25.792
Where the fuck are you, Avi?

16:25.792 --> 16:30.917
♪♪♪

16:35.500 --> 16:37.959
[siren blips]

16:40.542 --> 16:45.709
♪♪♪

16:48.875 --> 16:49.333
[cell phone rings]

16:52.000 --> 16:54.333
Where the fuck is Avi?

16:54.333 --> 16:56.333
I've been here 30 minutes
already.

16:56.333 --> 16:58.959
- I know.
- What do you mean, you know?

17:00.583 --> 17:02.500
Ray, I gotta tell you something.

17:02.500 --> 17:04.125
What?

17:04.125 --> 17:05.917
Avi just called
from the Eighth Precinct

17:05.917 --> 17:08.750
'cause he got arrested.

17:08.750 --> 17:11.917
Fuck are you talking about?
Arrested for what?

17:12.875 --> 17:14.583
For buying heroin.

17:17.458 --> 17:22.333
♪♪♪

17:23.041 --> 17:25.166
[siren whooping]

17:25.166 --> 17:28.166
[indistinct
police radio chatter]

17:35.625 --> 17:40.375
[sighs, laughs]

17:40.375 --> 17:43.834
I had some--this nerve pain

17:43.834 --> 17:47.458
from the beatings
the Russians gave me.

17:47.458 --> 17:48.250
[sighs]

17:48.250 --> 17:51.542
And we got the fentanyl
from them.

17:51.542 --> 17:54.458
I tried it. It worked.

17:54.458 --> 17:57.041
And then I needed more

17:57.041 --> 18:00.375
and different mixtures and...

18:03.542 --> 18:07.250
Fuck, Ray.
It just got away from me.

18:07.250 --> 18:11.250
I...I mean, what could I do?

18:11.250 --> 18:13.000
I was counting on you, Av.

18:14.917 --> 18:16.208
I know.

18:16.208 --> 18:19.667
I...I'm really fucking sorry.

18:20.750 --> 18:24.583
Look, uh...

18:24.583 --> 18:26.750
you bail me out.

18:26.750 --> 18:29.041
Twelve hours.

18:29.041 --> 18:32.792
I can connect
and w-work it out.

18:32.792 --> 18:34.458
I don't have 12 hours.

18:36.250 --> 18:37.709
I need that address.

18:37.709 --> 18:39.083
I can't.

18:39.083 --> 18:41.917
I can't.
She's Mossad katsas.

18:41.917 --> 18:45.333
She'll never engage with you.

18:45.333 --> 18:47.500
- She's in deep cover.
- I don't give a fuck

18:47.500 --> 18:49.083
what she is.

18:49.083 --> 18:50.667
Please, Ray.
[pounds on table]

18:53.000 --> 18:54.333
I want that
fuckin' address, Avi.

19:01.792 --> 19:04.458
- [Abby] Does it still fit?
- [Bridget] Yeah.

19:04.458 --> 19:07.500
I mean, we'll pin it
if it doesn't, but...

19:07.500 --> 19:10.208
it's beautiful.
[laughs]

19:10.208 --> 19:11.959
I wish I had
some fuckin' hair.

19:11.959 --> 19:13.792
[both laugh]

19:13.792 --> 19:14.250
I like this.

19:17.083 --> 19:19.125
How 'bout a red lip?

19:19.125 --> 19:20.625
You got it.

19:23.667 --> 19:26.709
- Is this good?
- Yeah.

19:26.709 --> 19:27.291
Okay.

19:29.834 --> 19:32.667
Go like that.

19:35.667 --> 19:37.583
I'm terrible.

19:37.583 --> 19:40.417
You have such pretty skin.

19:40.417 --> 19:41.959
It's your skin.

19:43.834 --> 19:45.500
Click 'em.
[smacks lips]

19:45.500 --> 19:47.417
Let me fix it.

19:47.417 --> 19:48.917
[sniffles]

19:48.917 --> 19:50.333
- Beautiful.
- [chuckles]

19:52.834 --> 19:55.792
So Dad is in New York, huh?

19:57.750 --> 19:59.792
- Yeah.
- Why is he there

19:59.792 --> 20:01.458
if you're not gonna
do the trial?

20:02.834 --> 20:05.333
Your dad's doing
what he has to do, sweetheart.

20:07.667 --> 20:13.375
Mom, I understand that you don't
wanna do that surgery, but...

20:15.542 --> 20:17.792
...no treatment at all?

20:17.792 --> 20:19.166
W-why not?

20:26.208 --> 20:30.250
It's like somebody's
chasing me.

20:30.250 --> 20:32.125
Like they're trying
to shoot me.

20:34.000 --> 20:37.333
But I wanna be the one
to shoot first.

20:37.333 --> 20:40.333
I wanna be the one
pulling the trigger.

21:00.125 --> 21:02.417
- This stuff too.
- Yes, of-of course.

21:11.542 --> 21:14.458
- [knock at door]
- [classical music playing]

21:14.458 --> 21:15.625
Hello.

21:16.291 --> 21:18.709
